### 1. [low] TypeScript package metadata still advertises 0.6.0
Refs: [src/ts/package.json:3](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-BUMP-20260524T205921Z/src/ts/package.json:3), [src/ts/package.json:4](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-BUMP-20260524T205921Z/src/ts/package.json:4), [docs/release-notes/0.6.1.md:6](/tmp/fdb-0.6.1-BUMP-20260524T205921Z/docs/release-notes/0.6.1.md:6)

The actual npm package version was bumped to `0.6.1`, but the published description string still says `TypeScript SDK for FathomDB 0.6.0`. Because `package.json` is shipped registry metadata and this file was already part of the release-touch set, this leaves stale user-visible versioning in the 0.6.1 artifact.

## What passed on inspection

